TY  - JOUR
AU  - Brunnermeier, Markus K.
AU  - Simsek, Alp
AU  - Xiong, Wei
T1  - A Welfare Criterion For Models With Distorted Beliefs*
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/qju025
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 129
IS  - 4
SP  - 1753
EP  - 1797
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This article proposes a welfare criterion for economies in which agents have heterogeneously distorted beliefs. Instead of taking a stand on whose belief is correct, our criterion asserts that an allocation is belief-neutral efficient (inefficient) if it is efficient (inefficient) under any convex combination of agents’ beliefs. Although this criterion gives an incomplete ranking of social allocations, it can identify positive- and negative-sum speculation driven by conflicting beliefs in a broad range of economic environments. 
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qju025
